The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Sunday, December 21, 2003 				 Gopal freed, gets SC notice
																								New Delhi, Dec. 20 (PTI): The Supreme Court has issued notice to the editor of Tamil magazine Nakeeran, R.R. Gopal, who was detained under the anti-terror law on a petition filed by Tamil Nadu government challenging a Madras High Court order granting bail to him. 																								The petition filed by the state government was mentioned before Chief Justice of India V.. Khare who assigned it to a bench of Justices R.C. Lahoti and Brijesh Kumar.																								The bench, without hearing any party, issued notice to Gopal and directed listing of the petition for hearing in the court on its reopening after winter vacation.																								The high court had yesterday directed that Gopal be set free, faulting the police with not providing any reasons for his arrest under IPC and the terror law. 																								The court held that Article 22(1) of the Constitution in clear and terms mandated that no arrested person shall be detained in custody without being informed of the grounds of such arrest as soon as possible.
